They would benefit from taking a step back and looking more carefully at the evolution of the steroid problem in baseball. An FBI special agent, Greg Stejskal, told the news media last month that he had notified Major League Baseball about 10 years ago that steroid use was a developing problem. But as baseball became more aware of this as a growing issue, the commissioner's office did, in fact, act. Indeed, it was probably around 10 years ago that some people in baseball became aware that anabolic steroids were being used by some players. 